        "title": "test: consolidate plugin registration contracts",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Consolidate bundled plugin registration contract wrappers into one table-driven suite.\n- Move extension-local registration expectations into the shared contract case table.\n- Delete duplicate extension and per-plugin core wrapper files while preserving registration coverage.\n\n## Verification\n\nPassed for this cleanup:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/contracts/plugin-registration.contract.test.ts`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --parallel-tests \"node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/contracts/plugin-registration.contract.test.ts\"`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nAdditional lint signal:\n\n- `node scripts/run-bundled-extension-oxlint.mjs` passed before the current base-branch Microsoft Foundry lint drift.\n- On the current base, the same bundled-extension lint command fails only in `extensions/microsoft-foundry/provider.ts`, outside this PR's diff.\n\n## Broad Extension Attempt\n\n- Testbox-through-Blacksmith `tbx_01kt0bsg5r8tzpkgmq9s43t3hz` ran `corepack pnpm test extensions` against this branch's synced content.\n- The broad run did not pass, but failures were outside this PR's touched registration-contract files:\n  - `extensions/matrix/src/matrix/monitor/events.test.ts`\n  - `extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-phases.test.ts`\n  - `extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-embedding-timeout.test.ts`\n  - `extensions/openrouter/music-generation-provider.test.ts`\n  - `extensions/ollama/src/stream.test.ts`\n  - final stuck/OOM state in `test/vitest/vitest.extension-codex.config.ts`\n- The previous unrelated `extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts` failure passed in this broad run.\n\n## Granularity Note\n\nThe one consolidated file still reports failures under per-plugin `describe` names from `describePluginRegistrationContract`, e.g. `<pluginId> plugin registration contract`, so the lost granularity is file-level only. The assertion names and plugin id remain visible in Vitest output.\n\n## Maintainer Decision Needed\n\nClawSweeper's remaining P1s are maintainer acceptance items rather than patchable defects:\n\n- **Test topology:** this PR intentionally removes per-plugin wrapper file paths. Accepting the PR means accepting centralized file-level discovery, with plugin identity preserved in `describe` names and assertions.\n- **Broad proof gap:** the broad Testbox extension run did not pass, but the observed failures were outside touched registration-contract files. Merge should either accept that gap for this test-only cleanup or wait for a refreshed broad extension run.\n\nCurrent CI also reports bundled extension lint failures in `extensions/microsoft-foundry/provider.ts`; those errors are unrelated to this PR's diff and come from the current base branch, not the registration-contract cleanup.\n",
